subSubSection.paragraph:
Common name. Norman did not give a common name for this species. The common name crying Izak was recently coined (Compagno & Human, 2003), and is in reference to the characteristic tear line markings, akin to those seen on the cheetah (
Acinonyx jubatus
), projecting from the anterior of the eye to the edge of the lateral surface in dorsal aspect.

Study material. BMNH 1939.5.24.2 holotype of H. melanostigma Norman 1939 , see under Type Series and Locality for details; BMNH 1939.5.24.3 and BMNH 1939.5.24.4 paratypes (not syntypes) of H. melanostigma Norman 1939 , see under Type Series and Locality for details;
RUSI 14114, previously PCH 80-15
, mature male 384mm TL, Fridtjof Nansen station 854 , 4°27’S 39°50’E , off Shimoni, Kenya .
